#: ../../../cmds/and.rst:14
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/and.rst:16
msgid ""
"``and`` is used to execute a command if the previous command was successful "
"(returned a status of 0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/and.rst:18
msgid ""
"``and`` statements may be used as part of the condition in an :doc:`while "
"<while>` or :doc:`if <if>` block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/and.rst:20
msgid ""
"``and`` does not change the current exit status itself, but the command it "
"runs most likely will. The exit status of the last foreground command to "
"exit can always be accessed using the :ref:`$status <variables-status>` "
"variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/and.rst:22
msgid "The **-h** or **--help** option displays help about using this command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/and.rst:25
msgid "Example"
msgstr "範例"

#: ../../../cmds/and.rst:27
msgid ""
"The following code runs the ``make`` command to build a program. If the "
"build succeeds, ``make``'s exit status is 0, and the program is installed. "
"If either step fails, the exit status is 1, and ``make clean`` is run, which "
"removes the files created by the build process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../cmds/and.rst:31
msgid "make; and make install; or make clean"
msgstr ""

